FBIS4-13224 "drnes075_k_94004" FBIS-NES-94-075 Daily Report 16 Apr 1994 IRAQ `Source' on Diplomats Assassinating Opposition Leader `Source' on Diplomats Assassinating Opposition Leader PM1804111494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 16 Apr 94 pp 1, 4 PM1804111494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT Arabic BFN [Unattributed report: "Two Diplomats Admit Assassinating Iraqi Oppositionist"] [Excerpt] Beirut, Paris, London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- An authoritative Lebanese source has said that the two Iraqi attaches detained on charges of assassinating Iraqi oppositionist Shaykh Talib Suhayl al-Tamimi in Beirut yesterday admitted killing the person in question on orders from Iraqi authorities. They also stressed during their interrogation in a police center in Beirut that they received the order to kill Shaykh Talib during their meeting with the Iraqi charge d'affaires in Beirut. According to well-informed sources, the two Iraqi diplomats will stand trial in Beirut if Iraq agrees to the Lebanese request to lift their immunity in accordance with the Geneva convention signed in 1961. [passage omitted]
